title: One step in front of the other
description:
HAH, I made it to the last one lads. 

This was actually first drawn for the blue period week, where I was genuinely in quite a funk and was thinking of Satoshi Kon's short "Ohayo", lamenting on how you still have to pull through each day and keep living even if it feels meaningless and stagnant.

I finished it in a totally different mood (aka after shitty exams) and wanted to express that in the colouring a little. Life gets tough and overthinking all the things you need to do gets daunting, but sometimes small things like morning air and sunlight can feel oddly grounding. Everything is hard but having to deal with it is almost comedic. 

PSA go listen to Japanese Breakfast's Paprika for music to soothe the Creative Struggle (the Satoshi Kon theme came back full circle weeks later).

I'm still experimenting a lot with CSP and its a fun ride! Thanks Cindy for having another cool and inspiring year of refresh, I really do appreciate it even though I couldn't do that many this year. Sending everyone who participated this year lots of love for all your hard work.

title: Reflection
description:
I thought it would be funny for the last week of the 2022 Design Refresh to point out that all my original songs had depressing lyrics this year:

- [Aquamarine](https://refresh.fiveclawd.com/works/szybttg5): Committing genocide during colonial imperialism then having flashbacks for the rest of your life.
- [See It My Way](https://refresh.fiveclawd.com/works/lbk0l6fy): A delusional happy-go-lucky idiot eventually fails to recognise their depression.
- [Something More](https://refresh.fiveclawd.com/works/0uic5g6v): Dying for your country without recognition, then being glorified for it in media.
- [Potential Energy (feat. Rin and Len)](https://refresh.fiveclawd.com/works/8mnkzvbf): "Have you ever wondered if the happiest day of your life has already passed?" and dying before you feel like you've lived up to your potential.
- [Salt Shores](https://refresh.fiveclawd.com/works/qplcto1y): A Viking raid murdering a bunch of farmers and lords, cutting their ears off in the process.
- [Carry On](https://refresh.fiveclawd.com/works/xwebdbaa): Crippling uncertainty before heading to university, and forgetting everybody you once knew.
- [Swansong (feat. Hatsune Miku)](https://refresh.fiveclawd.com/works/avskh71a): A physical relationship dying into a loveless marriage until one of them dies alone.
- [2007 Simulator](https://refresh.fiveclawd.com/works/g59lbydw): Living a dreary life on rails and "accepting" that we will study, work, then die.
- [Mist of the Sound](https://refresh.fiveclawd.com/works/e9kqzahv): The dying words of somebody who wished they didn't say "no" so much to their friends, who lived a boring, meaningless life.

Anyway, that's nothing to do with this submission.

You know, it's been about 6 months since I last recorded myself just playing guitar and singing cover songs. I figured for my last song that I would do a cover song by the person who inspires me most.

Link: https://online.fliphtml5.com/gqjmo/fpoj/

A compilation of poetry paired w/ flower illustrations for each prompt over the entire 15 week refresh. I wanted to keep this private until I was ready to show this in its completed form, mostly for my own sake. After a few hard personal + work related events, I realized that I wanted this to be my own way of grieving and healing while still keeping to the original refresh prompts and ideas.

This is also a small dedication to the people who have been standing alongside and inspiring me along the way, and that we aren't alone in this journey.

Note: BIG thanks to the friends who gave / created brushes for me to use + helped w/ research books, those who are been participating in the refresh, and ofc our design champion Cindy + web dev hero Papapastry. Imagine me slapping a huge bouquet of roses / whatever floral arrangement you prefer and aren't allergic to into your hands.

title: Blast from the Past (Part 1?)
medium: Clip Studio Paint + markers and cheap notebook paper
description:
Part 1 of my submission for this week! While looking through some old photos, I found pictures of my ancient sonic self-insert that I made when I was roughly 8-10 years old! And... yeesh! Not only did I not know how to draw, but I also didn't know I wasn't straight! How silly. I decided to take it upon myself and reimagine my old self-insert, drawing what little me would have wanted... and probably pissed their pants over if they ever saw it LMAO

I present a redesigned Sonic OC! Still don't really have a personality, but they look like the explorer type to me lol. In all seriousness, Sonic the Hedgehog is what inspired me to draw! I read a bunch of the Archie comics back in the day, and played mostly handheld Sonic games on the ds and 3ds... along with Sonic and Secret Rings on the Wii lol. While there are many other sources of inspiration in my life, I've been a fan of the blue blur for a long time! Maybe I'll read the IDW comic series sometime... and watch that new Netflix show and play the new game? Praying that those two are good...

Also, I included the old sonic OC drawings in addition to the redesign, you're welcome ;)

title: Cykk0
description:
So i've played quite a few genres of games growing up, from RTS, to first person shooters, MMO/RPGS, etc.
and in said 'CY'bernetic game worlds, you always got to just Keep 'K'illing everything down to zer'0'... like as if you were some sort of psycho.
when you're not sending a massive army to wipe out the enemy, you're committing genocide on the next local population of slimes  or animals that live peacefully around towns. the objective is almost always to drop your foes to zero.
Hence the name Psycho, or CyK0 (unfortunately not all games allowed 4 letter usernames so i had to add an extra K and just kept it consistent).

So if i had to make a logo based on said username, it would definitely have to incorporate ideas and elements on how i came to use said gamer tag.

So because logos typically need to consider printing, they usually need to be as minimalistic as possible to convey as much details as possible. Because there wasnt much to show, included the drafts to show the thought process on how i came to the final logo design. 
(touched up some details in MS paint after scanning)

fun fact, only afterwards i found out that some people read my username as sicko, which... i was alright with, it still incorporated the core idea on how messed up said game character would be if they were real, and i also do like making sick art.

title: Materialism girl!
description:
Strap yourselves in lads, we got a two-parter.

Aight, so firstly; Material Girl. The first thing that smash cut it's way into my brain was the song Material Girl by Madonna - for hopefully obvious reasons. Now I've played enough SingStar 80's to have the music video for that song permanently seared into my mind, but for those of you fortunate enough to not share this fate, Madonna in the vid is wearing this pretty pink number while dissing the simps that are throwing diamonds at her. 
Now the song is a disputable classic, but here's where the real history lesson kicks in. See the outfit she's wearing is an homage to Marilyn Monroe's look in the song "Diamonds are a girl's best friend" from the movie Gentlemen Prefer Blondes. 
So I drew a piece that played with that and pop art aesthetics that also vibe the concepts of consumerism and materialism explored in both songs.

Speaking of pop...

Surprise! 
I made another pop vinyl :P 
Now hear me out. This might actually be kinda clever. See I got inspired last week with the Mona pop and thought "what other classic art pieces could make interesting pops?" 
Enter the Girl with a Pearl Earring. Now if Blathers is to be believed, part of what made this piece special and unique was it's use of very expensive pigments for the eye catching blue turban. So what would happen if you take this classic and condense it into a mass marketable plastic collectable? 
I present the Pop with a Pearl Earring.

Okay I'm done. Please enjoy :)

title: 3 songs, 3 tragedies
description:
So... similar to the last piece, I used a limited color palette again (but more blue lol). For this one, however, I combined this week's prompt with another prompt. I was inspired by Drawfee's "Song Shuffle Drawing CHALLENGE" video where they took 3 songs from a shuffled playlist and drew 2 characters and the relationship between them. Technically I drew 3 characters here, but I'd say the shadowy figure isn't really the focus lol.

When I shuffled my own playlist I got "Bets Against the Void" by The Scary Jokes, "Honey I'm Home" by GHOST, and "Love Me, Love Me, Love Me" by Kikuo. Funny how I got two vocaloid songs lol, really shows my music taste. The first song I interpreted as the character being afraid of fading feelings and being forgotten. The second song tells a story about a person living a life within a cult, and the third one I read as being about a child desperate for love and affection from her parents, so she pushes herself to be good in school at the cost of her well-being. Taking all of that into account, I thought of two characters: a mother and daughter. The mother is a nun and part of a Catholic cult. One can assume she's manipulative and controlling but under the impression she is doing the right thing. The daughter is a non-believer, but she hides how she feels in fear of angering her mother and not receiving her love anymore. What happened to her father is up for interpretation, but he is represented by the shadowy silhouette.

Just as a disclaimer, this isn't to paint Catholicism as a whole in a negative light, just portraying one of the dark sides of religion. Also feel free to go listen to the songs I got and watch the Drawfee vid later! They good lol

title: Night Flight 2: Unexpressed
description:
This was one of the series of embraces I've had with you, who at this time I've cultivated some sort of closeness with you. As we were about to leave the office when you were about to book a ride home, you began to hug me, and this time, I've made it a point to hug you tightly, and lightly kissed you a few times, saying "love you lots" many times over.

It was as if, in that moment, I've finally expressed what I've failed to say and relay to the people I've valued over the decade and a bit past that. From my professor whom I've become good friends with, to the few crushes I've had over the years, my then office crush that I've only recently disclosed to you, in those series of embraces, I've finally said what I've always wanted to release outside of my shelled-in mind and heart prior to that time.

I remember watching Zhang Yimou's movie "Riding Alone for Thousands of Miles," and it made me remember this moment we had, and the culmination of feelings I've mistakenly hidden from everyone.

In a parting text message, you said that you were just a text away, and you were looking forward to seeing me progress, and catching up with coffee and tea. Of course, the global outbreak happened, but I look forward to the day I can embrace you again. You inadvertently gave me my first kiss weeks before, and on that night, I gave my first kiss to anyone.

For now, I can only reminisce. And keep things to myself.

title: Portrait 20: Living Water
description:
This type of art style is not my cup, but I tried anyway.

The pump is what we might refer to as a deep-water well, where water is pumped straight from the ground up. It's pretty straightforward: someone pulls down the lever to pump water up the ground.

For many places, it's the only way where people can get their water supply. It does have some negatives, such as the possibility of sinking land due to reduced groundwater underneath. But until water concessionaires step up to their agreements, water supply will always remain an issue for many communities, and an increasing reliance on deep wells.

The name is a reference to a village just beside our old provincial home, translated roughly to English as "Living Water" (Fil: "Buhay na Tubig"*; lit. "Water that has life").

*pronunciation guide [ENG]: "boo-high nah too-big"

title: Royal (WIP)
description:
(WIP clay sculpture~ I prolly wont be able to finish it coz of school stuff but here it is anyway.)

The Chinese Zodiac describe tigers as brave and fearless. Being the opposite of being fearless, I asked myself: When does ignorance and recklessness deviate from an act of bravery and fearlessness? More than likely, it is a mixture of the aforementioned and yet, all that matters every single time is the outcome. Fearlessness becomes noble when it results to positive outcomes. Yet it can be mocked as recklessness and stupidity when it amounts to nothing.

Often, when ends are used to justify whatever it took as "necessary" means, morality goes out of the window. So, what will it take to achieve an outlandish outcome? Where do we draw the line? It is easy to fall into the trap of assuming we know everything, sitting from high up. From there, we may label people as stupid for not sharing our royal stance. Eventually, we would start to think that we can decide for everyone's sake. Fearlessness becomes stubbornness and ignorance by then. Some may realize it early but most don't.

So, when we realize our ignorance, until when are we willing to push forward? Encapsulated by a Chinese proverb, "He who rides a tiger has need of great skill to dismount", implying the danger of justifying means through its outcomes is like riding a fierce tiger where we have no way to dismount without being devoured. Thus, it would seem that "we have no choice" but to see it through, right? Naaah, just get off your tiger and get a good car. LOL

Thought Reference: https://quoteinvestigator.com/2017/02/07/tiger/

description:
A Yangqin allows playing of several different types of pentatonic scale such as the Ionian pentatonic (AKA Ryukyu) scale, which is itself a mode of the Iwato scale. This scale has a very open and optimistic sound which I think is apt for the new year. The pentatonic scale is found cross-culturally in traditional music universally around the world, as are the variations.

A tiger is colourful and fierce like distortion and drums. A festival is upbeat but not necessarily joyous; the idea of an inevitable march of time is a common theme in my lyrics. Still, I did end up going "fuck it" for the second half of the lyrics after the bridge, so it's definitely demo quality and a WIP. No lyrics provided since it's WIP.

I included a YouTube video of the main song and an MP3 of the improv session I had to create the melodies.

title: Eyesoar
description:
If you are fortunate, until when is the conflict of the outside world a trivial eyesore if the windows only frame so little of the world beyond you? Till what distance can your eyes soar toward whether an external problem affects you or not? 

I think it's easy to spot whether someone does or doesn't genuinely care about any external issues beyond themselves. With the latter, they shut their doors close then only open their curtains to what they want to see or feel. Any attempts of discussion is dismissed upon immediate contact. Even if they do go closer to the window frame to see more of the view, it doesn't matter when their sight is colored and stained by bias.

What will it take to let the truth in then? Who gets to choose? I don't know.

title: Something More
description:
To me, a "window frame" reminds of what somebody would look at from their homes in a desire to explore. The characters in this tune have their purpose now, but it's never quite how it seems at the start. I connect this to the Age of Exploration fairly often because I feel like it will always be relevant to how we feel in our youth. And because ships and cannons and pirates and the sea are cool. Yes, I'm a grown adult.

Because there was no easy way for me to connect "window pane" to music theory, I did so in the themes:

- An old sloop would have its crew stay below deck looking through glass windows.
- Eyes are the "windows to the soul" so visual imagery and a reference to eyes appear in the themes of the song.
- Windows are made of glass and a spyglass is the signature object of an officer in a ship of this era.
- Glass is also fragile, and the characters singing clearly express their fragile uncertainty.
- Windows is also an operating system and I used my Ableton copy on Windows instead of on my Mac to write this song (and it only crashed twice!)
- _There's one more semi-hidden reference to windows. See if you can spot it!_

medium: Clip Studio Paint, Adobe Photoshop CC (3240x5400, 500dpi)
description:
The theme seemed rather simple, and a lot of ideas came to mind. Ultimately, I settled on this one, basing it on a poem by Filipino writer and labor leader Amado V. Hernandez titled "Isang Dipang Langit" (A Stretch of Heaven) written during his stay in a "bartolina" (a small cell for solitary confinement) while on trial for a 'complexed' rebellion case that later became landmark jurisprudence named after him.

The kite is my take on Filipino singer Celeste Legaspi's song "Saranggola ni Pepe" (Jose's Kite), a lullaby written during the dark years of Martial rule in the country containing cryptic lyrical imagery that require a second reading to be truly understood.

title: Amalgamation - Why Did I Hesitate To Say...?
medium: Clip Studio Paint, Adobe Photoshop CC 2015 (3840x2160, 400dpi)
description:
I've been feeling lonely during this time. I texted late at night and apologized to my leader, vaguely saying that things were "coming back to me." She said she could talk to her, or to you, since you were often at the office then.

I felt anxious, but asked for your time through an SMS app. You even said, "No, you (really do) need this :)" when I apologized for some reason.

Days passed by, but when we finally met, I couldn't help but smile at you. That very smile I've been holding back for months on end, hiding it from everyone else. We finally got to have that talk I needed.

When you were about to return to your station, I called you. But I forgot what to say. You even said then that we could talk again in another time. But that never happened, did it?

As I walked back, it became apparent. I had forgotten, hesitated even to say... that I loved you so much and you meant a lot to me.

By the time this appears on the showcase, it would've been your birthday.

Happy birthday. I love you still and I'll always miss you.

Spring, come unto me.

title: See it My Way
description:
"Meandering" has a lot of meanings to me: improvisation and jazz, sure, but also "walking melodies" that don't exactly use the call and response form of melodic phrasing. It's kind of like a melodic stream of consciousness.

"Mini Meanderings" directly evokes (to me) "happy-go-lucky" in a kind of sickening saccharine naivete. I want to keep things simple here. No philosophical storytelling of sorts, just a simple narrative of how much I want toxic positivity and those who exhibit it to explode.

The _other_ way I interpreted "mini" should be really obvious.

All instruments and voice were improvised. All I did with the vocals was run it a second time with a version of the lyrics I wrote from the random shit I mumbled the first time around, then improvised two vocal melodies.

title: Aquamarine
description:
As an audio submitter, I need to consider how to interpret themes that don't directly lend well to musical terms. Sometimes I'm forced to get a bit abstract:

- This is a kind of regal purple.
- Regal means "heavy, grand, complex, bold."
- This is a purple of the sea (thanks Heidelburgr for the suggestion).
- The periwinkle is a flower, which to me combined with "the sea" makes me think of the Age of Exploration.
- "Dots" reminds me of both staccato and waltz time (3/4).

Combining all these things together, I've created one of my most technically complex songs yet. It's definitely the hardest song to sing that I've ever written.

Give it a few listens and see if you like it!

title: Amalgamation: Look-Back
description:
I probably have said a few times how much Takeshi Kitano's 1997 movie "HANA-BI" (Fireworks) have inspired me to begin drawing again, but I guess this one perfectly represents it, with the purplish hues and everything like the film, fit for the week's theme.

This is me revisiting my first semi-serious attempt at art from December 2019, finished on February 2020, where I first started to just put dots from my ballpen, then buying felt markers and a gel pen, until I saw that it came out to my liking.

I was afraid back then some of my friends would find out it was my then-office crush that was the subject, hence the beginning of the series "Amalgamation". It was the beginning of my journey in art, and more importantly, a way to process my emotions, like the supporting character Horibe, a former cop that became a wheelchair user who took up painting as a hobby (all the paintings in the movie were painted by Takeshi while recovering from a motorcycle accident in 1994).
